ls: The ls command in Linux is used to list files and directories present in current working directories.
ls -l: This command gives detailed list of contents in that directory.
ls -la: This commad displays all the files including hidden files.
pwd: This command displays the content that is currently running in directory.
cd: cd command is used to change current working directory.
clear: It clears everything on the terminal.
mkdir: It is used to creat new directory.
cp: cp command is used to copy files or directories.
mv: It is used to move or rename files and directories.
rm: It is used to remove or delete fies permanently.
uname: This command is used to display system information.
locate: locates command is used to find files using a database.
touch: touch command is used to create empty files.
cat: This command is used to display file contents.
ps: The ps command is used to display running processes.
man: The man command is used to display command manuals.
grep: It is used to search text patterns.
sudo: It is used before a command to run it with administrative privilages.
df -h: This command is used for human redable output.
sed: It search and replace a pattern in a file.
